{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019CwzCVg5ARcooN1HPPAprt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I understand the full picture. I need to:\n\n1. Generate TLS certificates\n2. Create `es-http-tls` secret and `elastic-password` secret  \n3. Update the ConfigMap for ES 8.11.1 (add security + TLS settings + cluster.initial_master_nodes)\n4. Delete the existing StatefulSet and PVCs (to start fresh with 8.11.1)\n5. Deploy new StatefulSet with ES 8.11.1\n6. Wait for pods to be ready\n7. Verify HTTPS connectivity\n\nLet me proceed.\n\nFor the seed_hosts, the current config uses short forms like `es-cluster-0.es-cluster`. \n\nI should use fully qualified domain names to be safe since the reminder mentioned seed_hosts may have drifted to invalid values. With the headless service `es-cluster` in the `elasticsearch` namespace, the pod DNS names would be `es-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`, `es-cluster-1.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`, and `es-cluster-2.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`.\n\nNow I'll generate the TLS certificates and create all the necessary resources.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5438,"cache_read_input_tokens":34106,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5438},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3d89b8e-7c20-4f1d-b88b-8ffa026ed71e","uuid":"df5d80ef-78e5-449a-935e-8ee577c0fe18","request_id":"req_011CcepzCNH1Ntq3mkXY49g4"}
